1.title: Zombie King of the Prom
1.plot: Audra and Wednesday are hunting down a costume accessory for the King of the San Francisco Zombie prom. Meanwhile the shop gains a new employee, Lincoln, who must help find an item to soup up a customers "time machine" that runs on electrical impulses.

2.title: Funeral Parlor Games
2.plot: Wednesday gets a request from an artist who has a death obsession. Her hunt takes her to the home of an artist who relishes making people vomit. Meanwhile, Audra has her hands full when a customer stops by with a family heirloom that's beyond gross.

3.title: Heads Up
3.plot: When a collector of tribal artifacts stops by Loved To Death, Audra and Lincoln must hunt down an item that will impress this hard-to-please customer. Meanwhile, Wednesday shows a woman the perfect addition to her vintage fetish collection.

4.title: Walk Like an Egyptian
4.plot: An illustrator tasks Wednesday and Audra with finding an Egyptian artifact. Wednesday's hunt takes her to a skin suspensionist and a woman whose trailer is a museum. Meanwhile, Audra meets Violet who possesses the world's only toy-theater top hat.

5.title: Mind Games
5.plot: At Loved to Death, Audra & Lincoln meet a doctor with an extensive medical collection who's looking for a brain-related wow item. Wednesday meets Jelly Boy the Clown who swallows swords but is looking for an item to help with an extraction.

6.title: Soul Fire
6.plot: At Loved to Death, Audra and Wednesday are asked for a torture related item that's fit for a king. Later, Lincoln shows a customer one of the most dangerous toys ever created and Audra investigates if a customer's mummified monkey is a relic of the past.

7.title: Take This Job and Skunk It
7.plot: At Loved to Death, a biker who has an odor problem comes in with one of the strangest requests yet. Wednesday shows off a mechanical hand to someone who had a bad time at Burning Man. Later Lincoln meets someone looking to sell an ancient Peruvian skull

8.title: One Bot, Two Bot
8.plot: Wednesday looks at robots for identical twins. She meets up with a builder whose robots are named Darwin and Schizoid. At Loved To Death, Audra checks out a quack hair growth device and Lincoln meets someone who makes music using an unusual body part.

9.title: Full Steam Ahead
9.plot: Wednesday and Audra head to Vallejo, California in search of steampunk items for the store and to attend an Alice in Wonderland themed, Mad Hatter Parade. At Loved to Death, Lincoln encounters Kung Fu Vampire and a tattoo artist who freeze-dries cats f

10.title: Give the Dog His Bones
10.plot: Kari Byron from Mythbusters stops into Loved to Death, with a special request of a skeletal nature. Wednesday helps a woman looking to add to her vintage fetish collection and researches a model of the solar system with some help from The Urban Astronome

1.title: Shock the Monkey
1.plot: At Loved To Death a patron injects new life into what it means to be a pin-up girl. Then Audra & Korri search for an item suitable for an organ grinder and get bowled over by a real life bone collector, while Wednesday is introduced to mental floss.

2.title: Holy Hydrocephalic Cow
2.plot: At Loved To Death gears are cranked and teeth are pulled as the team tries to find trophies fit for a steampunk Major. Then a customer sells a cow with more on its mind than milk, while Audra & Korri visit a sidowshow performer who sets the house on fire.

3.title: Miniature Monstrosities
3.plot: At Loved To Death a customer sells Wednesday a gas mask that's a horse of a different color. Then a collector commissions Audra to craft a diorama combining taxidermy and biological weapons, while a mysterious man brings in an even more mysterious skull.

4.title: Vile Style
4.plot: At Loved To Death, Wednesday & Korri combine heads to find a macabre item for a local designer's photo shoot. Then Audra dares to sink or swim when buying a supposed antique diving helmet, while a jar of mystifying animal remains could spell trouble.

5.title: Eye, Robot
5.plot: At Loved To Death, Wednesday sets her gears in motion to find a vintage automaton for an artist. Then, Audra and Korri find a friendly face buried in the depths of an Odd Fellows lodge, and an imbiber of blood tries to sell a cannibal utsensil.

6.title: Cobra-Cadabra
6.plot: At Loved to Death, Audra & Korri work their magic to track down a serpentine oddity for a local illusionist. Then, Wednesday makes a trade that wins her a seat on a live electric chair, and a customer reveals just how many legs it takes to sell a cow.

imdb.plot outline: San Francisco puts a West-Coast spin on Science's mega-hit series ODDITIES. The show follows crazy transactions as big, odd memorable characters come in out of the famed store Loved To Death, located in the heart of San Francisco. The shop's cases and walls are overflowing with rare scientific curiosities; there's something for everyone on the sales floor. This oddball staff led by shop owner, Audra, is always leaving the shop to hunt for more strange and obscure pieces to add to the inventory. Unique items and customers cycle through their doors each day, in addition to the wild experiences that happen outside the shop's walls: This cast of characters have come to expect the unexpected.
